The paper deals with learning multilingual word representations, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The use of autoencoders is also a common technique in NLP and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training and evaluating models, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of bag-of-words representation and document classification suggests the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as possible but less likely sub-categories.
